  "summary": "makecoder postinstall executes shell commands via curl/powershell at install time",
  "details": "The package's scripts/postinstall.js (line 6 onward) requires child_process and invokes execSync with curl and powershell command lines, causing arbitrary shell activity to fire automatically on `npm install`. The bundled dist/ tree additionally contains code that branches network behavior on host/ping checks and POSTs to hardcoded endpoints including `https://geminicli.com`, while wrapping references to legitimate domains (ai.google.dev, registry.npmjs.org, youtube.com) as cover. The combination of a postinstall lifecycle hook driving curl/powershell execution plus hardcoded non-publisher destinations contacted from bundled code constitutes install-time remote code execution against any developer or build system that installs this package. The package name pattern (impersonating coding-assistant tooling) and the geminicli.com endpoint, distinct from Google's official ai.google.dev SDK domain, indicate brand impersonation rather than a legitimate Gemini integration.",
